Emarr <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gorgirmgrudgebearer>Gorgirm Grudgebearer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 55<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 12:52 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: King Tormax and stuff</span><hr size=1> Statue, Tormax, Kland, Rumblecrush, Doomshade, Lcea, Eashen, LTK,  <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91906>Veteran  Gorgirm Grudgebearer</a><BR> Dwarven Warlord of The Kindred<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tamria>Tamria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 1:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: King Tormax and stuff</span><hr size=1> As long as you can kill Vindi under control (i.e. he's routine and not russian roulette that he dies before your clerics go OOM and your tanks get whacked) then Tormax isn't as big a leap up as many think. <br>
<br>
Statue you should definetly do - the only hassle you should have is if you get the quadding version and have trouble slowing him quickly.<br>
<br>
Dain is another good target - tricky working out the pull and probably a different kind of fight to what you're used to if you been focused on CH rotations, MTs and prox aggro control lately.<br>
<br>
Cazic-Thule is fun to - even clearing Fear AE-style (assuming you have a couple of good chanters and some nukers) can be a laugh.<br>
<br>
Other than that you've got the standard CoV stuff and the lesser SoL stuff (Ragh 2 for starters then maybe IV).<br>
<br>
But for sure think about Tormax - I remember being paranoid about trying him after hearing a lot of horror stories about how he's so much harder than Vindi, he isn't - just you won't be able to kill him if you zerg Vindi and only manage to kill him with a bit of luck. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=leavandoreq>LeavandorEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 1:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: King Tormax and stuff</span><hr size=1> Tormax has the same DPS as Vindi roughly, but has a lot more hp? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reghar1>Reghar1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 2:27 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: King Tormax and stuff</span><hr size=1> Tormax hit for a little less, 585ish on me max while Vindi hits me for about 765 max.  Both hit fast and often and are unslowable.  Both Rampage.  Tormax just has a truckload more HP.<br>
<br>
Tormax and Statue are honestly the next logical step if you want to keep CoV.  Dozekar is right there as well.  Finish up some HoT quests.<br>
<br>
After you get those mobs down you might want to learn IV/Grieg/RC/Doom.  RC is a great mob to learn rampage on.<br>
You will need to understand rampage before you move up to high end Ssraa. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=426241"target=new>Reghar is so Money<a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ranxerex>Ranxerex</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/11/02 5:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: King Tormax and stuff</span><hr size=1> my guild is in the same situation...<br>
<br>
We have taken down Vindi 5 times, the first couple tries were really rough (learning pull, controlling rampage).. but after the first win (some luck involved) we have taken him down without much of a struggle with 20 characters - 26 characters(lots of bots ;p).<br>
<br>
We have killed Gozz (11 playeres, 19 characters), Telk, Velk, Vindi, and we just took down Dozekar..<br>
<br>
My question is this,  King Tormax quads 580, unslowable, has how many hps?  we take down Vindi with 24 chars in just under 4 minutes (when defense wears, I still don't really beserk often with a /pause 42 ch rotation).  Is he 300k? 400k?  I would use a 5 second ch rotation on Tormax (single tank the whole way), we use 4 clerics on rotation and with a 5 second rotation could get near 9 minutes of a chain before the clerics went OOM.  <br>
<br>
In the past, we have just went up and tried the mobs until we figured it out, but this mob is a bit different, there is STILL a huge race for tormax ;/.  I don't want to set up a rotation thats goin to just flat out fail and us lose the chance to kill such a significant mob.  I am MT with 7100 hps buffed, 1400something ac, SoD mainhanded for agro..  I have ND3, CA 3, CS 3, PE, AT, Ambidex, PD1,  Will i be able to sustain the dmg for a 8 minute fight?  will it take twice as long as Vindi?  his rampages i have heard are notorious (as in 3 target rampage, unlike vindi's 2 target..),  is his rampage hit list larger?  <br>
<br>
Any help appreciated,  I am hoping what i am guessing to go in with will work but any reassurance is nice!<br>
<br>
Thanks,<br>
<br>
